First publish (one-time, before OIDC can be configured):

  npm login
  make build
  npm publish --access public

After the package exists on npm, set up OIDC:
  1. npmjs.com → @justestif/pk → Settings → Trusted Publisher → Add GitHub Actions
     Owner: justEstif  Repo: pk  Workflow: publish.yml
  2. Toggle 'Require OIDC' (small radio button — easy to miss)
  3. Delete the temp token

Subsequent releases:
  npm version patch|minor|major
  git push origin main --tags
  Create GitHub release from the tag → triggers publish.yml automatically
